1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:37,203
Chiara is already in Prague.

2
00:00:37,287 --> 00:00:38,371
That's why what you're saying
is impossible.

3
00:00:39,414 --> 00:00:41,249
<i>She was at Sir Norberto's house earlier.</i>

4
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:44,377
It has been confirmed by Carlota.

5
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:50,550
Open your eyes to the truth

6
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:53,928
that your greatest enemy here
is the person you love.

7
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:55,680
I said that's enough.

8
00:00:56,806 --> 00:00:57,724
Mikoy!

9
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:00,977
You know, Chiara was right.

10
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:03,146
I really need to be careful with you.

11
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:06,232
You're doing all of this to break us up.

12
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:07,567
Because you like me.

13
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:12,822
Who are you really?!

14
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:24,250
You went to Mikoy?

15
00:01:29,339 --> 00:01:33,384
You went to Mikoy and told him,
that Chiara is La Fornarina.

16
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:37,388
Our asset's security has been compromised.

17
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:38,306
So I had to warn him.

18
00:01:43,394 --> 00:01:46,689
When we turn a witness we bring them here.

19
00:01:51,194 --> 00:01:52,612
But what did you do?

20
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:55,031
You dumped Carlota here.

21
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:57,492
Then you went straight to Mikoy.

22
00:01:58,076 --> 00:01:59,536
Didn't you hear me?

23
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:02,747
I had to warn Mikoy.

24
00:02:02,831 --> 00:02:04,958
Because Viktor suspects him.

25
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:06,960
No. What you did was,

26
00:02:07,043 --> 00:02:10,338
you told him that Chiara is La Fornarina.

27
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:17,387
Okay? You wasted everything
we started, Alex.

28
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:22,392
I built this case.

29
00:02:22,892 --> 00:02:25,270
So if anyone's
bringing down the Moravianos,

30
00:02:25,353 --> 00:02:26,354
it's me!

31
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:30,608
Do you want us
to start counting our sacrifices now?

32
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:33,820
The hardships
we've endured for this mission?

33
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,615
That Mikoy could already be compromised.

34
00:02:37,699 --> 00:02:41,369
And if it's true that
Chiara is La Fornarina.

35
00:02:41,452 --> 00:02:43,163
There's no way Mikoy doesn't know that.

36
00:02:43,246 --> 00:02:44,497
There's no way he doesn't know

37
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:47,458
that the woman
he shares a bed with every day

38
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:50,211
could be the ultimate Moraviano.

39
00:02:50,295 --> 00:02:51,629
And someone who could
become the future leader

40
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:54,716
of the biggest syndicate
we may never be able to bring down.

41
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:13,484
Because clearly,
you're not listening anymore.

42
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:15,737
You're blind and deaf to the truth.

43
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:17,739
If you remove me from this case,

44
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:20,283
then you're also
protecting the Moravianos.

45
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:31,294
You're the one who should stand down.

46
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:32,795
Why don't you try?!

47
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:35,965
Try to disarm me
and let's see what happens.

48
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:36,883
You're too…

49
00:03:36,966 --> 00:03:38,635
- attached to Mikoy.
- What's going on here?

50
00:03:58,321 --> 00:03:59,364
What's the problem?

51
00:03:59,447 --> 00:04:01,866
- Sir.
- What's happening with you two?

52
00:04:05,495 --> 00:04:06,496
Really?!

53
00:04:06,996 --> 00:04:09,082
I just turned one Moraviano agent.

54
00:04:09,165 --> 00:04:11,125
If we're counting contributions,

55
00:04:11,209 --> 00:04:13,795
every breakthrough in this case
came from me.

56
00:04:13,878 --> 00:04:15,922
We're here because of me.

57
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:18,925
And you have the nerve to say
that I'm hurting this mission.

58
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:20,176
Alex.

59
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:26,182
But with what you're doing now,

60
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:28,393
you're the one ruining this case.

61
00:04:33,731 --> 00:04:37,652
You're prioritizing Mikoy
instead of taking down the Moravianos.

62
00:04:38,861 --> 00:04:40,113
How am I compromised?!

63
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:42,865
Because you're too blind to see

64
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:45,368
that Mikoy could already
be a Moraviano now.

65
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:46,577
That's enough!

66
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,164
You two.

67
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:53,751
You're going to destroy this agency.

68
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:55,920
So stop it already!

69
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:05,179
Especially in front of the agents.

70
00:05:06,597 --> 00:05:08,808
What happened to your teamwork?

71
00:05:17,525 --> 00:05:20,987
You're arguing in front
of all these agents.

72
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:24,365
You two are so concerned in this case

73
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:28,619
that you're dragging everyone down
by demoralizing the team.

74
00:05:40,006 --> 00:05:40,923
Go ahead.

75
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:58,209
You know, son.

76
00:06:59,293 --> 00:07:01,295
I used to have a simple dream.

77
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:08,344
For you not to experience the hardships
I went through.

78
00:07:16,602 --> 00:07:18,396
<i>But it seems I was wrong.</i>

79
00:07:18,479 --> 00:07:21,065
I never wanted you to carry this burden.

80
00:07:34,495 --> 00:07:35,663
<i>If only I could take it back,</i>

81
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:38,749
I wouldn't let this happen.

82
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:41,544
<i>If I could only turn back time,</i>

83
00:07:41,627 --> 00:07:46,632
I would never let this happen.

84
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:49,677
But we can't change that anymore.

85
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:55,349
So starting now…

86
00:07:58,102 --> 00:07:59,520
I'm here.

87
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:07,153
<i>You, Angelito, and your mother</i>

88
00:08:07,236 --> 00:08:08,905
are who I will choose.

89
00:08:28,007 --> 00:08:30,259
<i>I will never leave you, son…</i>

90
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:33,638
Mikoy.

91
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:37,266
In every battle you face.

92
00:09:25,856 --> 00:09:28,568
You're like a daughter to me, Agent Alex.

93
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:31,153
So let me ask you.

94
00:09:36,492 --> 00:09:39,996
Is it true that
you are losing your goddamned mind?

95
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:47,003
Agent Sianong is right.

96
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:55,052
You're becoming very unpredictable.

97
00:09:56,929 --> 00:09:59,223
First, you let Carlota go.

98
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:05,479
Then, you gave information to our asset
about his girlfriend.

99
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:09,525
Information that has not been verified.

100
00:10:11,944 --> 00:10:14,447
How did Mikoy react?

101
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:17,533
He wasn't happy, right?

102
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:21,370
Why did you do that?

103
00:10:23,789 --> 00:10:25,416
Is it true?

104
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:27,918
That you're getting attached to him?

105
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:32,757
That you're falling for him
and starting to like him?

106
00:10:37,011 --> 00:10:38,512
Don't answer that.

107
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:41,515
I don't care about your feelings.

108
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:45,311
I care about you as an agent.

109
00:10:48,105 --> 00:10:52,652
I want a complete rundown
of where we are in this case.

110
00:11:00,701 --> 00:11:04,664
NORBERTO S. RUIZ
GENERAL

111
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:26,018
And there's something in the oven.

112
00:11:26,602 --> 00:11:28,062
Please take it out and put the dish in.

113
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:30,064
Bring it upstairs too, thank you.

114
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:46,956
Yes, I may have overdone it a little.

115
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:49,667
Viktor.

116
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,293
Our daughter.

117
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:53,963
I'm not used to seeing her like this.

118
00:11:55,589 --> 00:11:58,134
What do we need to do?

119
00:12:30,082 --> 00:12:31,375
Hey, I have a girlfriend.

120
00:12:31,959 --> 00:12:33,919
Yes, I know you love Chiara.

121
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:35,921
But wake up, Son.

122
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:38,424
Mom! Mom.

123
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:41,802
Were you surprised, Son?

124
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:43,846
Wait.

125
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:47,600
Wait, why are you still sleeping
when it's already noon?

126
00:12:47,683 --> 00:12:48,642
Don't you have work?

127
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,520
But before you answer that.

128
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:54,023
I cooked breakfast
and we're having a feast.

129
00:12:54,106 --> 00:12:55,357
So get up now.

130
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:56,358
Come on.

131
00:12:57,735 --> 00:12:58,736
Hurry up.

132
00:14:27,032 --> 00:14:28,534
I know you're all worried.

133
00:14:28,617 --> 00:14:31,912
About the consecutive attacks
from the Moravianos.

134
00:14:37,835 --> 00:14:40,796
And if you think
we're just going to stand here

135
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,007
and take all their attacks.

136
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:02,026
Well.

137
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:10,993
It wasn't life-threatening,
but it still hurt.

138
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:14,371
That's why
she went to my house to recover.

139
00:15:14,955 --> 00:15:16,290
I took care of her, sir.

140
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:18,459
I even made her rice porridge.

141
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:21,503
I also cooked her my favorite dish, adobo.

142
00:15:22,296 --> 00:15:23,797
But the thing is, sir.

143
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:27,468
I had a hard time deciding
what kind of adobo to make for her.

144
00:15:27,551 --> 00:15:29,678
Because there are many kinds of adobo.

145
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:33,265
There's white adobo
with vinegar with soy sauce.

146
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:35,392
There's also adobo with sauce.

147
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:38,479
But it's not debatable
whether it's paksiw or adobo.

148
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:40,314
But of course, what I made was.

149
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:49,406
He was able to provide us

150
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:53,535
actionable intelligence that will lead us
to a secret center

151
00:15:53,619 --> 00:15:58,499
where they process their
illegal operations.

152
00:16:10,094 --> 00:16:13,055
As hard as Pacquiao's right hook!

153
00:16:14,348 --> 00:16:15,683
With all due respect, sir,

154
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:17,810
Pacquiao's left hook is the killer blow.

155
00:16:17,893 --> 00:16:20,854
Do you also want to get hit
by Pacquiao's right hook?

156
00:16:30,114 --> 00:16:31,490
This stays between us.

157
00:16:32,199 --> 00:16:33,909
Just between us.

158
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:37,079
Because I have a secret when making adobo.

159
00:16:38,372 --> 00:16:39,748
My secret is…

160
00:16:40,457 --> 00:16:43,460
I add one or two drops

161
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:48,382
of 50-year-old Balsamico Di Modena.

162
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:05,941
You're making excuses.

163
00:17:07,943 --> 00:17:09,278
No.

164
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:12,156
Would I really hide the truth from you?

165
00:17:12,239 --> 00:17:14,742
The Viktor Valtrovi?

166
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:43,479
Already dead?

167
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:45,814
Can't you torture me first?

168
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:48,233
At least stab me in the eye, sir.

169
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:49,526
Good grief.

170
00:18:16,053 --> 00:18:18,388
Just hearing your voice makes me tremble.

171
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:20,099
It's just that

172
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:22,309
there's someone scarier than you.

173
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:42,246
Sir, I could see the anger in her eyes.

174
00:18:42,329 --> 00:18:45,666
You know she'll do anything
just to get rid of what she's feeling.

175
00:18:49,711 --> 00:18:51,088
I'm a father too.

176
00:18:51,588 --> 00:18:53,423
So I understand you.

177
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:56,510
Sir Viktor,

178
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:58,637
I also have a daughter.

179
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:02,182
And when she feels that way,
I would do everything

180
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:04,810
just to make her feel better.

181
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,868
This isn't our fight.

182
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:25,289
There are things that no matter what we do
we can't help Chiara with.

183
00:19:28,792 --> 00:19:32,129
Only she can know what she should do.

184
00:19:43,307 --> 00:19:45,350
I was surprised by your father.

185
00:19:45,434 --> 00:19:48,896
I only called him to ask
how the land he was fixing was going.

186
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,898
Then suddenly,
I was surprised when he said

187
00:19:50,981 --> 00:19:53,275
he was coming back to Manila,
so of course I followed right away.

188
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:54,276
That was the only way

189
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:56,987
to make sure I can see
my two troublemakers, right?

190
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:58,989
Now you, Mario.

191
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:02,492
You should finish dealing
with that land already.

192
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:04,995
At this rate,
it'll just end up as potted soil.

193
00:20:05,078 --> 00:20:06,788
You can never tell.

194
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:10,959
Angelito, thank you so much
for joining us today.

195
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:12,336
You had time for us.

196
00:20:12,419 --> 00:20:13,670
How's school going?

197
00:20:13,754 --> 00:20:15,422
Oh! right.

198
00:20:15,505 --> 00:20:17,549
What's the name of his girlfriend again?

199
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:19,426
Sofie!

200
00:20:19,509 --> 00:20:22,596
You know, I know all those Gen Z labels.

201
00:20:22,679 --> 00:20:24,139
That's right, labels.

202
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:25,682
Do you two have labels now?

203
00:20:25,766 --> 00:20:27,392
Or are you just vibing?

204
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:30,395
See? I know what I'm talking about.

205
00:20:30,479 --> 00:20:32,397
Do you know what?

206
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:34,650
Cebu misses you all so much!

207
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:36,735
Betchay misses you so much.

208
00:20:36,818 --> 00:20:39,154
The drinking sessions miss you all
with what's-his-name again?

209
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:40,656
Who was that again? What's his name?

210
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:41,782
Oh, Dekyo.

211
00:20:41,865 --> 00:20:44,284
Everyone misses you,
so when are you going on vacation?

212
00:20:44,368 --> 00:20:45,702
That's what I'm saying.

213
00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:46,912
Angelito.

214
00:20:46,995 --> 00:20:51,750
You are not allowed to enroll
in summer classes

215
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,336
because I don't want you
getting stressed, Son.

216
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:56,004
Think about it.

217
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,965
You know the word "burnt out"?

218
00:20:58,048 --> 00:20:59,258
I don't want that happening to you.

219
00:20:59,341 --> 00:21:00,884
Okay? So go on a vacation.

220
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:02,552
Okay? Promise me that.

221
00:21:02,636 --> 00:21:04,554
Mikoy, I just thought of something.

222
00:21:05,055 --> 00:21:10,352
Why don't you bring Chiara? To Cebu!

223
00:21:10,435 --> 00:21:12,145
We have so many
beautiful beaches there, right?

224
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:14,523
What's the name
of that beautiful beach again?

225
00:21:15,357 --> 00:21:17,567
Bantayan Island.

226
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:18,735
I just thought of something.

227
00:21:18,819 --> 00:21:23,198
Let's also bring Donabel and Viktor too!

228
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:26,618
Mikoy.

229
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:28,495
Where's Chiara?

230
00:21:28,578 --> 00:21:30,080
You know, I noticed something.

231
00:21:30,163 --> 00:21:33,417
I've been here for a while,
but I haven't seen her.

232
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,418
Where is she?

233
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:38,588
Mom, Chiara is in Prague.

234
00:21:38,672 --> 00:21:40,632
She just has something
she needs to take care of.

235
00:21:45,012 --> 00:21:46,596
You should've gone with her.

236
00:21:48,223 --> 00:21:49,182
Wait.

237
00:21:49,266 --> 00:21:52,519
You didn't go with her,
or she didn't want you to?

238
00:21:52,602 --> 00:21:54,980
Oh, dear, Son. Tell me the truth.

239
00:21:55,063 --> 00:21:56,565
Tell your father and me.

240
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:58,442
Are you two okay?

241
00:21:58,525 --> 00:22:00,527
Are you having problems?
Tell us the truth.

242
00:22:02,195 --> 00:22:03,488
Mom, we're okay.

243
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:06,408
We're getting along fine.

244
00:22:06,491 --> 00:22:08,035
Chiara's just really busy.

245
00:22:10,037 --> 00:22:11,705
But she'll come back.

246
00:22:14,541 --> 00:22:15,375
Let's eat now.

247
00:22:15,459 --> 00:22:17,169
Enough with all the talking.

248
00:22:17,252 --> 00:22:19,421
You all talk too much.

249
00:22:19,921 --> 00:22:21,631
<i>I'm a father too.</i>

250
00:22:21,715 --> 00:22:24,009
<i>So I understand you.</i>

251
00:22:25,802 --> 00:22:27,179
<i>Sir Viktor,</i>

252
00:22:27,679 --> 00:22:30,140
<i>I also have a daughter.</i>

253
00:22:30,223 --> 00:22:32,017
<i>And when she feels that way,</i>

254
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:36,563
<i>I would do everything</i>
<i>just to make her feel better.</i>

255
00:22:38,065 --> 00:22:44,404
VALTROVI

256
00:22:50,327 --> 00:22:54,664
<i>There are things that no matter what we do</i>
<i>we can't help Chiara with.</i>

257
00:22:58,210 --> 00:23:01,296
<i>Only she can know what she should do.</i>

258
00:25:25,941 --> 00:25:28,235
What?! Mikoy? I don't understand.
What did Mikoy do?

259
00:25:41,581 --> 00:25:43,792
Copy, Mother Eagle. Let's go.
